rest_of_day_open: I have this coming week off work so I'm pretty happy about that. I'll just do regular relaxing stuff earlier as my husband will still be at work. Then on Thursday we're going camping/backpacking for a few days so I'm really excited to get away from it all and spend time in Yosemite National Park
critical_positive: We had something in common starting off about the Prolific app and how it worked. She had actually done this chat before so knew a bit about how it was supposed to go down. And we both were cat lovers so shared photos of our cats and what they are like. Also we like Disney/Pixar movies
critical_negative: It was a bit artificial - since we weren't provided any conversational prompts, we had to think of things to talk about which weren't too personal. We didn't even exchange names, I felt she didn't want to give up too much information about herself, which is totally fine by me! But it was different even than what you might do if you met someone at a party or event

rest_of_day_open: I see the rest of my week being somewhat busy but still enjoyable overall. I will be working, doing household cleaning, and running errands. Tomorrow I have to take my spouse to the dentist. The day after that I have to run errands. And the day after that I will need to get groceries.
critical_positive: We were both open and friendly and that helped our conversation flow easily. Our common interests of animals and animated films also helped our conversation go well. We both took an interest in the other and tried to keep the conversation equal and balanced between us. All of these things helped.
critical_negative: It was hard to tell when the other person would begin or end their speaking. It can be difficult to interpret what other people are thinking and feeling over video chat as well. There was a certain amount of lack of common experiences as well that made the conversation somewhat hard.
